# Catering Client

Premium Angular 17+ standalone app for a catering service. Consumes REST API at `http://localhost:3000/api`. Luxury dark theme: gold/black/white palette.

**Stack:** Angular 17+ (signals, standalone) | TypeScript strict | SCSS | HttpClient | RxJS

## Collaboration — Read First

Two developers work in parallel. **Respect ownership boundaries.**

### Do NOT modify (Dev 1 — core infrastructure)

- `src/app/app.config.ts`, `src/app/app.routes.ts`
- `src/app/core/guards/` — auth, admin guards
- `src/app/core/interceptors/` — auth, error interceptors
- `src/app/core/models/` — User, Dish, Package, DTOs
- `src/app/core/services/` — auth, token, toast services
- `src/app/features/auth/`, `src/app/features/profile/`
- `src/app/shared/components/navbar/`, `footer/`, `toast/`
- `src/environments/`

### Your scope (Dev 2 — features, UI, design system)

- `src/styles/` — design tokens, typography, base components
- `src/app/features/dishes/`, `packages/`, `home/`
- `src/app/features/admin/admin-dashboard/`
- `src/app/shared/components/dish-card/`, `package-card/`, `loader/`

Need a new route? Dev 1 owns routing — coordinate before adding.

## Commands

```bash
npm install && ng serve    # http://localhost:4200
npm run build && npm run test
```

Backend must run: `npm run dev` in `catering-server/`

## Angular Patterns

- **Standalone only** — no NgModule; explicitly list all imports
- **Signals:** `input()`, `output()`, `signal()`, `computed()` — prefer over RxJS subscription chains
- **Strict TypeScript** — zero `any`
- **Control flow:** `@if`, `@for`, `@switch` (not `*ngIf`/`*ngFor`)
- **Auth:** JWT injected by `auth.interceptor.ts` — never attach tokens manually
- **Admin check:** `authService.isAdmin` signal — no hardcoded role checks
- **Feedback:** `ToastService.success()` / `.error()` for user messages
- **Models:** use existing types from `src/app/core/models/` — do not redefine

